avia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Of Celtic origin and uncertain derivation (possibly a diminutive of a word meaning ‘rock’). It was introduced into England by  Breton  followers of  William the Conqueror , most notably  Alan , Earl of Brittany, who was rewarded for his services with vast estates in the newly conquered kingdom. In Britain the variants  <b>Allan</b>  and  <b>Allen</b>  are considerably less frequent, and generally represent transferred uses of surname forms, whereas in America all three forms of the name are approximately equally common.  See also  Alun ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Halenald \"Alan\" d'Alneto was born about 1110, in Turvey, Bedfordshire, England, his father, Sir Henry d'Alneto, was 52 and his mother, Agnes de Lisours, was 19. He had at least 1 son with Mrs Halenald Alan de Alneto Sir. He died after 1172."},"et":{"about 1110–after 1172":"umbes 1110–pärast 1172","1110–1172":"1110–1172","1112–Female":"1112–Surnud","1130–1225":"1130–1225","1060–Male":"1060–Surnud","1093–Female":"1093–Surnud","1225":"1225","1112":"1112","after 1172":"pärast 1172","1110":"1110","1130":"1130","about 1110":"umbes 1110","1172":"1172","1093":"1093","1060":"1060","Turvey, Bedfordshire, England":"Turvey, Bedfordshire, England","Turvey, Bedford, England":"Turvey, Bedfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1110–after 1172":"noin 1110–1172 jälkeen","1110–1172":"1110–1172","1112–Female":"1112–Kuollut","1130–1225":"1130–1225","1060–Male":"1060–Kuollut","1093–Female":"1093–Kuollut","1225":"1225","1112":"1112","after 1172":"1172 jälkeen","1110":"1110","1130":"1130","about 1110":"noin 1110","1172":"1172","1093":"1093","1060":"1060","Turvey, Bedfordshire, England":"Turvey, Bedfordshire, England","Turvey, Bedford, England":"Turvey, Bedfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1110–after 1172":"environ 1110–après 1172","1110–1172":"1110–1172","1112–Female":"1112–Décédée","1130–1225":"1130–1225","1060–Male":"1060–Décédé